value.0: "Hello again. What can I do for you?" Serah smiles up at you.
This woman has an open, friendly face, creased with the lines of one who has lived through some hard times.
"Welcome to the office of the Landowners' guild, good <sir/madam>. My name is Serah Blackhand. How may I help you today?"
"Be wary, friend. These are hard times."
"Well, we don't have any farmland available at the moment. Too many violent monsters ruining the crops and eating the livestock. Most of the landowners have sought safety here in the keep."

Comment.value: if PC has not introduced self

"I am sorry, but I don't even know who you are. Maybe if I knew a little about you, I could make a judgment call in this matter."

value.0: "Most definitely. These are not rumors... whatever ghosts or spirits live in there are always there, and no one has survived entering. No one goes in there anymore."
"But I figure you seem a lot tougher than my average customer, so I'll give you a price cut on the house. It is more of a mansion and was supposed to sell at 10,000 gold."
"I'll give you the keys for a mere 2000 gold, but you have to drive the ghosts out yourself."
"Oh, I guess I misjudged you then. Sorry. It's not a problem, I just thought it would help your position in the election."
"If you change your mind, just come back and ask me about it again."
"Well, I'd like to just give it to you, but there are taxes owing on it. A lot of debt has been accumulated that needs to be paid off. If you need gold, you should speak to The Stan."
"He's right across the hall and he pays well. I doubt the house will sell too quickly, so come back and ask me about it later.

Comment.value: give key to haunted house, take 1000 gold, set journal entry

value.0: "It sure will be nice to get those debts paid off and be rid of the old place. Manybrick Manor was a beautiful home once. I hope you enjoy it... after the ghosts are cleaned out."
"I know that's a lot of gold. You should go and speak to The Stan. He is right across the hall, and he pays quite well. Good luck, <FirstName>."
"Oh, it was a while back now. The woman who lived there went insane. She threw herself off a cliff, if I remember correctly."

"Her sister sold the house to pay off the woman's debts but the buyers died in a gruesome fashion not a fortnight later, drowned in saltwater on the upper floor. Some say it was from the madwoman's tears."
"I asked, but Lavos said that if Mistress Death chose to return a few souls to haunt some house, who was she to argue? Perhaps you can do a better job of convincing her than I was able to."

Comment.value: If PC knows about haunted house.

value.0: "Are you interested in buying the haunted house for 2000 gold?"
"Why yes I am! You must be <FirstName> then. I have heard some good things about you and am pleased to meet you."
"Sweet Alias needs as many friends as she can get. She spends too much time wandering on her own. So what can I do for you today?"
"I am always pleased to be able to help. What would you like to know?"
"Right. Is there anything else I can do for you?"
"Most of my interests lay outside of town, but I will do my best to help you."
"They're on my property and I want them off! That's what I know. If you want more details on them, I would suggest speaking to Feran in the Military Guild."
"The Mossy Tree and the Silver Lily are both decent establishments, if you want a short term place to stay. I am the person to speak to if you want to purchase a more permanent home."
"Talk to Levio'Sa. She often has unusual goods from outside of town. Southpaw runs the Pawnshop, so you might look there as well. Look around, there are plenty of merchants."
"The Stan runs the trades guild. You can find him in his shop, The Trades, or in the trades guild office, in the Guildhall."
"Well, as master of the guild, my job is to try to protect the other landowners from rising taxes, to sell land or houses as necessary, and to keep accurate records of the commons."
"Any open grounds within the keep are property of the keep. Families are contracted to care for the commons, raising grains and animals, in case the keep is ever besieged."

"Often the families work off debts by working the commons, which means the keep doesn't have to pay for the labor. It generally works out for the benefit of all, bringing in new landowners and increasing our tax base."
"Not very much. There was quite a bit of land available after the keep's army left us, but most of it sold to families from the south, expatriated slaves and criminals."
"When you get this far north of civilization, you don't ask a lot of background information. That's why I represent these people. Many of them are very private."
"Those who are poor can pay off some of their land by working the commons. Right now we have plenty of workers, with the landowners staying in the keep until the Masked Man's forces are dealt with."
"She is a sweet child, with a pleasant disposition that really rises above the tragedies she has had to face. Her mother died while she was just a babe."
"She was only about eleven when her father went off to war, and like all the other soldiers, he was never heard from again."

"I have tried my best to raise her right, but she is a loner. It is good that she has you to work with, because she usually works alone. I would suggest you talk to her if you want to know more. Anything else?"
"Right, down to business. Your interest in this is keen, I imagine."
"Our guild usually meets and votes, then I take their decision to the guild vote. I do have enough influence to sway the guild vote, however."
"Did Alias tell you anything about the troubles I have been having lately?"
"Ha, isn't that the truth. The girl can talk, that's for sure. She is much like my sister... was. But that is a different topic.  Back to my present troubles."
"Well, you might want to pay attention this time. If you help me with my problem, I can convince the other landowners that you are our best hope."
"If you can rid me of the goblins, I will do all that I can for you."
"Since you have helped me out, I see no reason why I shouldn't help you out. Killing those goblins proves you have what it takes to help the landowners out in these troubled times."
"Our vote is for you, may you have luck in the running. What else would you like."
"Yes, after the siege on the keep was broken, the remaining forces turned tail and ran, losing all their spine with the Masked Man's death."
"We tracked a band of his goblins to a cave on my property and, just this morning, a number of my cattle have started to go missing."
"I am glad you are so confident, but there is more you should know."
"Three of my personal guards figured that they were tough enough to go into the caves and take care of the goblins. They never returned but we heard a loud rumble shortly before noon."
"The goblins must have set up a trap to kill or capture any pursuers. I went to the military guild and Feran said he would assist me, but he was overruled."
"That argument is foolish! We provide much of the food that the residents of the keep need to survive. If you hope to become the <Lord/Lady> of the Keep, you had best learn some diplomacy!"
"Before his death in the recent battle, the Banner had noted the increase in monster sightings in the area. He increased funding to the militia to train more guards."

"Those who lived outside the walls were invited to bring livestock into the keep and live here until the troops were ready. Unfortunately, the assault on the keep came sooner than we hoped and many of the recruits were killed."
"If you were to do something about the Masked Man's forces, I could make sure you have our vote, as well as the time to sway a few more supporters."

"If you are unwilling to do this, that is your choice. I suppose that means I shall have to vote for Enivid. Hopefully she will be able to exterminate the Masked Man's forces before they do the same to us."
"I am fairly busy right now, so if you change your mind, feel free to return. For now, I have to get back to work."
"My duties here in the guild also include the selling of property. There is a place for sale that would normally cost around ten thousand gold. There are a few problems with the house though."
"Prove your abilities and I will cut the cost of the house considerably. If you really want to be the <Lord/Lady> of the Keep, you should set up a permanent home here."
"Thank you, <FirstName>. If you are capable of doing this, then you have the ability to become a strong ruler. Actions speak louder than words, I always say."
"If you don't want to have to search for the proper cave, I would suggest you speak to Alias. I am sure she would be pleased to lead you right there."
"Otherwise, my property lies to the east. The goblin caves are not far from my house. Was there anything else you needed?"
"Well, eventually someone is going to have to, but not yet. If you were to clear the goblins out of their cave, the other landowners would know you were serious and capable of helping them."

"By the Hand, Enivid... The woman means well but she's too cautious by far. The militia's spread thin to be sure but there must be someone among the guard who can be spared from the walls to protect the outlying lands."
"They are all dead then? Do you have something to prove what you say?"
"A grizzly trophy, but one that definitely proves the job was done. I imagine you will find me here, whenever you are finished."
"I thought it was pretty self-explanatory. Anyone can say they did the job, even if all they did was enter the caves, see some goblins, did unseemly things in their armor, then ran away."
"What a disgusting thing. Very well, I will keep it to show the other landowners, to prove your worth to them."

"Now, for your reward, here is the 200 gold, and you are now our candidate for the election. I can also hold off the election three times for you. I will have Alias come and get you if a vote is called."
"Good. If you decide that you would like a permanent place here in Cyan, I have a house I can give you a real deal on. Sure, it has problems, but I think it might be perfect for you."
"Well, there is a house for sale. Showing that you have long-range plans in the Keep by purchasing a house would probably help your position."

"The problem is that the only house we have right now has several problems. First it is an expensive, old house. I can help you there, since it hasn't sold in the four years it has been on the market."
"Well, that is all I have to offer. If gold is the problem, you should speak to The Stan. He's right across the hall and he pays well. If you should change your mind, all you have to do is ask."
"If you don't have enough support, then you won't win. I should think that is obvious. The more people get to know and respect you, the more likely they are to vote for you."
"Most guild masters will tell you that nothing could convince them to vote for you, but don't believe it. Everybody has a price. Everybody."

"An important vote can be held off three times, if guilds are not ready to vote yet. Most guild masters don't take advantage of this, but I do, because my guild is notorious for being slow to reach a decision."
"Everyone is used to my petitions for time, so they won't suspect anything if I do it for you. They'll just think my fellow landowners are being difficult again."
Serah raises an eyebrow in your direction, frowning at the same time.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "Flatterer! I guess an old woman needs a little flattery, sometimes. You must be Alias's friend. It is nice to meet you."
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> Suddenly she breaks into a mischievous smile. "Good. We need a leader with some spirit. You must be Alias's friend. It is nice to meet you."
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> She shakes her head and sighs. "Young people these days... Even Alias is more mature."
"Alias speaks well of you, so I shall struggle to overcome this first impression you have left me with and greet you as a family friend."
Calibast laughs. "Good start there, <FirstName>. You can't even inspire an old woman!"
Serah turns an icy glare towards Calibast, whose chuckle slowly dies.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> She chuckles at your bravado. "Alright now, enough fooling with an old lady. You must be Alias's friend. It is nice to meet you."
"Oh yes, I should have recognized you, from all the descriptions I have heard. You have certainly impressed many people, including my niece."
"So how do you like the house? I hope everything is going smoothly for you. Good luck in the election."
"Good day, kind Lord. How may my humble office assist you today?" Serah smiles warmly as she offers you a formal curtsy.
"You own the castle now, m'<lord/lady>, there is nothing I can offer that is half so fine. Sorry."
"Goodbye."

"It's haunted?"
"I don't want a haunted house!"
"I don't have that kind of gold."
"I'll take it."
"How did it get to be haunted?"
"Why hasn't the church done anything about it?"
"Are you Alias's aunt?"
"I would like to ask you some questions."

"I have questions about the keep."
"Let's talk about something else."
"What do you know about the Masked Man's forces?"
"Where can I get a room?"
"Where can I get equipment?"
"Where can I find employment?"
"What does your guild do?"
"Lets talk about something else."
"What are the commons?"
"Do you sell a lot of land?"
"Tell me about Alias."
"Let's talk about the election."
"She said a lot of things. I might have missed it."
"If she did, I wasn't paying attention."
"No, she never said anything about troubles."
"I was told you have a goblin infestation."
"An entire tribe of goblins is no match for my prowess!"
"And you were afraid of some weak goblins?"
"So why haven't the local guards done anything about it?"
"They have to protect the keep, not those who chose to live outside it."
"Cowardice! Who would do such a thing?"
"I don't think so."
"I would need more reward than that."
"The goblins are already dead."
"I will do it."
"I have to kill all of the monsters?"
"Overruled by whom?"
